titlestmt.titleproper: Commonwealth Fund records, Grants, SG 2, Series 10
A Guide to the Commonwealth Fund records, Grants, SG 2, Series 10 FA1448

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2020-03-13 00:38:54 -0400.

did.unittitle: Commonwealth Fund records, Grants, SG 2, Series 10

physdesc.extent: 123 letter-size document boxes, 2 legal-size document box.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Records remain in original order, as received.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

Researchers interested in accessing digital media (floppy disks, CDs, DVDs, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact an RAC archivist.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Commonwealth Fund records were donated to RAC in 1985. The initial transfer of archival records to RAC began in 1986, and transfers continue on a regular basis. These specific grant files were transferred to RAC in multiple accessions in 2013-2015.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: RAC has legal title, copyright and literary property rights to this collection in so far as it holds them.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Minimal processing, 2018. Some records remain in original file folders.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Each grant file often contains records pertaining to: budget and administration, proposals and development, articles and background information, correspondence, grant products and related program files. The grants represented in this series primarily span 2000-2010.
